data.chText: 不用于进行时
data.enText: not used in the progressive tenses

data.chText: 包括；包含；由…组成
data.enText: to have sb/sth as parts or members

data.chText: 这部画册收有327幅画。
data.enText: The collection comprises 327 paintings.

data.chText: 委员会由政府和私人部门的双方代表组成。
data.enText: The committee is comprised of representatives from both the public and private sectors.

data.chText: 是（某事物的）组成部分；组成；构成
data.enText: to be the parts or members that form sth

data.chText: 在那些生活贫困的人中，老年人占有很大的比例。
data.enText: Older people comprise a large proportion of those living in poverty.

data.text: consist of ♦ comprise ♦ make up ♦ constitute ♦ be composed of ♦ be comprised of ♦ compose

data.chText: 以上各词均表示由某些人或事物组成，或构成某事物。
data.enText: All these words mean to be formed from the things or people mentioned, or to be the parts that form sth.
consist of sb/sth

data.chText: 指由事物、人或活动组成、构成：
data.enText: to be formed from the things, people or activities mentioned

data.chText: 他们的日常饮食以蔬菜为主。
data.enText: Their diet consists largely of vegetables.
comprise

data.chText: 指由…组成、构成：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) to be formed from the things or people mentioned

data.chText: 这部画册收有327幅画。
data.enText: The collection comprises 327 paintings.

data.chText: comprise亦可指组成、构成：
data.enText: Comprise can also be used to refer to the parts or members of sth.

data.chText: 在那些生活贫困的人中，老年人占有很大的比例。
data.enText: Older people comprise a large proportion of those living in poverty.

data.chText: 不过这种用法不常见。
data.enText: However, this is less frequent.
make up sth

data.chText: 指组成、构成：
data.enText: ( rather informal ) to be the parts or people that form sth

data.chText: 女生占学生人数的56%。
data.enText: Women make up 56% of the student numbers.
constitute

data.chText: 指组成、构成：
data.enText: to be the parts or people that form sth

data.chText: 40岁以下的人占劳动力的大多数。
data.enText: People under the age of 40 constitute the majority of the labour force.
be composed of sb/sth

data.chText: 指由…组成、构成：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) to be formed from the things or people mentioned

data.chText: 我们的饮食中大约有15%的蛋白质。
data.enText: Around 15% of our diet is composed of protein.
be comprised of sb/sth

data.chText: 指由…组成、构成：
data.enText: to be formed from the things or people mentioned

data.chText: 委员会由政府和私人部门两方的代表组成。
data.enText: The committee is comprised of representatives from both the public and private sectors.

data.chText: 有人认为这种用法不正确，更喜欢用comprise的主动语态。
data.enText: Some people consider this usage incorrect, and prefer to use the active verb comprise .
compose

data.chText: 指组成、构成：
data.enText: ( formal ) to be the parts of people that form sth

data.chText: 基督教徒大约占这个国家人口的2.5%。
data.enText: Christians compose around 2.5% of the country's population.

data.chText: 词语辨析
consist of是这组词中最通用、也是唯一可与动词-ing形式连用，表示包含…活动的词：
data.enText: Consist of sb/sth is the most general of these words and the only one that can be used for activities with the -ing form of a verb.

data.chText: 我那时的工作只有打信。
data.enText: My work at that time just consisted of typing letters.

data.chText: 另一个主要区别在于有些词是将整体作为主语，部分作为宾语：
data.enText: The other main difference is between those verbs that take the whole as the subject and the parts as the object

data.chText: 这个小组由十个人组成。
data.enText: The group consists of/comprises/is made up of/is composed of/is comprised of ten people.

data.chText: 另一些词则是将部分作为主语，整体作为宾语：
data.enText: and those that take the parts as the subject and the whole as the object.

data.chText: 这个小组由十个人组成。
data.enText: Ten people make up/constitute/comprise/compose the group.

data.chText: 用comprise of或be composed by/from均不正确。
data.enText: It is not correct to use ‘comprises of’ or ‘is composed by/from’.
which word?

simple_means.memory_skill: com 加强 + pris 抓 + e →〔包括〕抓住的东西 → 包括

ex.chText: 我们小组由10位专家组成。
ex.enText: Our team is composed of ten experts.
Water is composed of hydrogen and oxygen.

ex.chText: 众多商号构成了我们经济中的商业部分。
ex.enText: A large number of firms compose the business sector of our economy.

synonyms.bx: 指由两个或更多的人或物形成一个整体，多用于被动语态，常后接介词 of。

ex.enText: A cutlery set is comprised of 6 table knives.

ex.chText: 兼职人员中妇女占有很大比例。
ex.enText: Women comprise a large proportion of part-time workers.

synonyms.bx: 既可指整体包含若干部分，也可指若干部分或成员构成整体。

ex.chText: 我们班由20位男生和15位女生组成。
ex.enText: Our class consists of/is composed of 20 boys and 15 girls.

ex.chText: 我的早餐通常是面包、果酱和牛奶。
ex.enText: My breakfast consists of/is composed of bread, jam and milk.

synonyms.bx: 指整体由两个或更多的人或事物构成，常可与 be composed of 换用。

ex.chText: 这两党组成了一个联合政府。
ex.enText: The two parties constituted a coalition government.

synonyms.bx: 指由某些部分组成一个整体。

example: This money is my only income
The stone wall was the backdrop for the performance
The children made up the chorus
This sum represents my entire income for a year
These few men comprise his entire army
A totally new idea is comprised in this paper
The record contains many old songs from the 1930's
The land he conquered comprised several provinces
What does this dish consist of?

value.def: If you say that something comprises or is comprised of a number of things or people, you mean it has them as its parts or members.

example.ex: The special cabinet committee comprises Mr Brown, Mr Mandelson, and Mr Straw...
example.tran: 特别内阁委员会包括布朗先生、曼德尔森先生和斯特劳先生。

example.ex: The exhibition comprises 50 oils and watercolours...
example.tran: 展览陈列了50幅油画和水彩画。

example.ex: The task force is comprised of congressional leaders, cabinet heads and administration officials...
example.tran: 工作小组由国会领导人、内阁首脑和行政官员组成。

example.ex: A crowd comprised of the wives and children of scientists staged a demonstration.
example.tran: 由科学家们的妻儿们组成的队伍举行了示威游行。

value.def: The things or people that comprise something are the parts or members that form it.

example.ex: ...the multitude of ideas, ambitions and regrets that comprises the culture of Russia today...
example.tran: 构成现今俄罗斯文化的众多观点、抱负和遗憾

example.ex: Women comprise 44% of hospital medical staff.
example.tran: 女性占医院医护人员的44%。
